Product Id: The type of commodity shipped. Groupings based on the Standard Classification of Transported Goods (SCTG) two-digit level.
This combines the Standard Classification of Transported Goods (SCTG) codes 01, 02, 03 and 04.
This combines the Standard Classification of Transported Goods (SCTG) codes 05, 06, 07, 08 and 09.
This combines the Standard Classification of Transported Goods (SCTG) codes 10, 11, 12, 13 and 14.
This combines the Standard Classification of Transported Goods (SCTG) codes 16, 17, 18 and 19.

This combines the Standard Classification of Transported Goods (SCTG) codes 30, 34, 35, 38, 39 and 40.

The aggregate number of shipments transported. For air and truck, a shipment represents the movement of a single commodity from an origin to a destination. For rail this represents the number of cars.
The aggregate weight of the shipments.

The aggregate revenue that the carrier earned from transporting the shipments. For rail the revenue value is based on attributing the revenue to the shipments based on tonne-kilometres of the shipment and the overall revenue without distinguishing carrier, geography and much commodity detail. The revenues are not specific to a market and should not be used as a benchmark.
The aggregate distance that the shipments were transported.
The weight of each shipment multiplied by the distance transported and then aggregated.
The aggregate value of the shipments.
